<FIRST>r a BC-BRF--TeenKilled     10-15 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-BRF--Teen Killed,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Teen-ager Shot When Gun Accidentally Discharges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLAY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 14-year-old boy was killed Saturday when a
friend holding a handgun accidently fired the weapon into the
youth's chest, police said.
   Michael Steber of Clay died at about 6:15 p.m. from a gunshot
wound to the chest, according to Robert Burns of the Onondaga
County Sheriff's Department.
   Detectives said Steber and two friends were alone at a home
owned by Gordon Lane when the shooting occurred shortly after 6 p.m.
   Steber was shot once with a .38-caliber automatic handgun in a
bedroom the private two-story house, Burns said.
   Steber was dead at the scene when fire officials and paramedics
arrived, police said.
   The two other youths who were with Steber were questioned, Burns
said, but no charges have been filed. Burns said the shooting was
accidental.
   Police refused release the names of the two friends, their
relationship with Lane or say who owned the weapon.
