<HEAD>Two Die in Hot Air Balloon Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hot air balloon carrying sightseers
struck some power lines north of Sydney on Sunday and crashed,
killing the pilot and a passenger, police said.
   The pilot was a electrocuted and a female passenger died of
internal injuries, said a police spokesman who did not identify
himself. He said three other passengers escaped uninjured.
   The balloon was flying over the Hunter Valley vineyards, about
80 miles north of Sydney, when it crashed.
   The accident was the fourth involving hot air balloons in
Australia in the past two months. Thirteen people died Aug. 13 when
their balloon collided with another and and two people died
Wednesday when a balloon hit power lines near Mudgee, 112 miles
northwest of Sydney.
   Six passengers were hurt a week ago when a balloon crashed into
a hillside north of Melbourne.
