<FIRST>r i AM-DancerDisappears     10-15 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Dancer Disappears,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviet Dancer Disappears in Spain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet dancer disappeared last week from
a hotel in Madrid, where he was performing with a Soviet dance
troupe, a newspaper reported Sunday.
   The newspaper El Pais said Vladimir Karimov, 39, had been
missing since Friday. He was here with the Soviet Union's Red Army
Choir and Dance Troupe.
   The newspaper reported that the dance group noted his
disappearance about 8:00 a.m. Friday. After awaiting several hours
for him they decided to continue their trip to Portugal, where they
were scheduled to perform.
   Police said the disappearance of the Soviet dancer would be the
first step in asking for political asylum but that they had not
heard from him.
</TEXT>
