<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Alcoa     10-15 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Alcoa,0147</SECOND>
<HEAD>Alcoa Profit Down 23 Percent, Sales Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Aluminum Co. of America reported a 23 percent
decline in profit in the third quarter, though its sales increased.
   Alcoa said Friday it earned $219 million, or $2.46 a share,
compared with $226.3 million, or $2.56 a share, posted in the third
quarter of 1988.
   Sales totaled $2.8 billion in the third quarter, up 11 percent
from the $2.6 billion in the third quarter of last year.
   The company said its third-quarter profit included unfavorable
foreign currency adjustments of $15.3 million, or 17 cents a share.
   For the first nine months of 1989, Alcoa earned $780.2 million,
or $8.79 a share, compared with $642.7 million, or $7.27 a share,
in the 1988 period. Year-to-date revenues totaled $8.2 billion, up
15 percent from $7.1 billion in 1988.
</TEXT>
